title: Printer's Sample Book, 1866–69
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs for printed textiles. Contains 36 samples of printed cottons.
